<br>
Hell is defined as an eternity without God.  It's not about fire,brimstone- that was devised in radical puritan sermons that pilgrims attended if for nothing else to keep warm in midwinter.  Dante also wrote about it for a good kick too.  Both of these are the results of our own culture- nothing more.<br>
<br>
If you don't want to be part of heaven, which means being with God (I suppose the love of the omnipotent force is quite &quot;heavenly&quot;), then you want hell, which means being away from God.  This is what Lucifer, aka Satan (which translates to &quot;rival&quot; or &quot;opponent&quot;), recieved in his goal to be as powerful as god.  Isolation.  The only references to anything nasty comes with Revelations- where Satan and his minions are to be thrown into a pit of flame.  At least, that's what I remember from Catholic school. ^_^<br>
